I"þ<h1 id="definition">Definition</h1>
<p>There are multiple definitions of the concept fusion ring in the literature, often with subtle differences. On the AnyonWiki the following definition is used.</p>

<p>A â€˜â€˜fusion ringâ€™â€™ \((R,+,\cdot)\) is a ring with unit \(\psi_1\) for which the following axioms are fulfilled:</p>

<ul>
  <li>The underlying abelian group \((R,+)\) is a free abelian group.</li>
  <li>
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>There exists a finite set $$B = {\psi_i</td>
          <td>i\in I} \subset R$$ such that</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <ul>
      <li>\(\psi_1\in B\),</li>
      <li>\(R=\mathbb{Z}B\),</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>for all \(i,j \in I\) \(\ \psi_i \cdot \psi_j  = \sum_{k\in I} N_{i,j}^{k}\psi_k\), where \(N_{i,j}^{k} \in \mathbb{N}\), and</li>
  <li>there exists an involution \(i  \mapsto i^*\)  such that \(N_{i,j}^{k} = N_{i^*,k}^{j} = N_{k,j^*}^{i}\) (Frobenius reciprocity).</li>
</ul>

<p>Immediate consequences:</p>

<ul>
  <li>The fact that \(\psi_0\) is a unit reformulates as \(N_{i,0}^j = N_{0,i}^j = \delta_{i,j}\) for all \(i,j \in I\), which reformulates as \(N_{i^*,j}^0 = N_{j,i^*}^0 = \delta_{i,j}\) by Frobenius reciprocity.</li>
  <li>The associativity of the ring reformulates as: for all \(i,j,k \in I\)
\(\sum_{s \in I} N_{i,j}^s N_{s,k}^t = \sum_{s \in I} N_{j,k}^s N_{i,s}^t\)</li>
</ul>

<h1 id="frobenius-perron-dimension">Frobenius-Perron dimension</h1>

<p>The involution \(*\) provides a \(*\)-algebra structure on \(\mathbb{C}B\), given by \(\psi_i^* =  \psi_{i^*}\).</p>

<p><strong class="label">theorem</strong>
<em>(Frobenius-Perron theorem)</em>: there is a unique \(*\)-homomorphism \(d: \mathbb{C}B \to  \mathbb{C}\), with \(d(P) \subset \mathbb{R}_{&gt;0}\).</p>

<p>The number \(d(\psi_i)\) is called the â€˜â€˜Frobenius-Perron dimensionâ€™â€™ of \(\psi_i\), and is noted \(\mathrm{FPdim}(\psi_i)\). The Frobenius-Perron dimension of \(R\) is the number \(\mathrm{FPdim}(R):= \sum_i \mathrm{FPdim}(\psi_i)^2\).</p>
